teeth is a 2007 black comedy horror film written and directed by mitchell lichtenstein .   the movie stars jess weixler and was produced by lichtenstein on a budget of us$ 2 million .   the film premiered at the sundance film festival on january 19 , 2007 , and was distributed by roadside attractions for a limited release in the united states .   despite being positively received by critics , the film had an international box office gross of $ 2,340,110 , barely earning back its budget .   at sundance , weixler received the grand jury prize for acting .   the film has a plot based around a dawn o'keefe , a woman with teeth in her vagina , who sets out to take vengeance on all men who have wronged her after being raped .